{"key":"processedPost-14975330","value":{"id":14975330,"first":14969916,"last":26676608,"when":1314283339,"utime":"08/25/11 05:42 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />so harvest the first mushies, pins and all, off the cake once<br /></blockquote><br /><br />No.<br /><br />You pick individual mushrooms as they're ready.&nbsp; Never pick all the pins off a cake unless you just don't like allowing them to grow to full size. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/shrug.gif\" alt=\":shrug:\" title=\":shrug:\"/><br /><br />Most strains don't fruit in nice, neat, orderly flushes where all the mushrooms grow together and mature together.&nbsp; If you want that kind of performance, you'll have to learn to <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Strain-Isolation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">isolate strains on agar</a> and grab a strain with those qualities.&nbsp; With multispore inoculation, you might have 20 or more active strains in one substrate.&nbsp; Each strain is going to fruit on its own schedule.&nbsp; Picking pins off simply ruins everything.<br />RR","title":"Re: Harvesting pins with the mature shrooms","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}